### Variables
@host = http://localhost:4004
@adminAuth = Authorization: Basic admin:admin
@organizerAuth = Authorization: Basic organizer:organizer
@attendeeAuth = Authorization: Basic attendee:attendee

### ================
### Catalog service (open — no auth required)
### ================

### Browse all events with the venue and sessions data
GET {{host}}/odata/v4/catalog/Events?$expand=venue,sessions

### Try to create an event (should fail — 405 Method Not Allowed)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/catalog/Events
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "This should fail"
}

### ================
### Admin service
### ================

### Browse all events with everything expanded
GET {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events?$expand=sessions,registrations,venue
{{adminAuth}}

### Create new event (draft-enabled — creates an inactive draft)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "BTP Developer Day 2026",
    "description": "A one-day hands-on workshop for BTP developers",
    "startDate": "2026-10-15T09:00:00Z",
    "endDate": "2026-10-15T17:00:00Z",
    "maxCapacity": 100
}

### Try to create an event with invalid dates (validation fires on draftActivate)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "BTP Developer Day 2026",
    "description": "A one-day hands-on workshop for BTP developers",
    "startDate": "2026-10-15T09:00:00Z",
    "endDate": "2026-10-12T17:00:00Z",
    "maxCapacity": 100
}

### Check events in admin service (should show attendeeCount and seatsRemaining)
GET {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events?$select=title,maxCapacity,attendeeCount,seatsRemaining
{{adminAuth}}

### ================
### Request chaining — create → activate → publish
### ================

### Create a draft event and capture the response
# @name createEvent
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Chained Test Event",
    "startDate": "2026-11-10T09:00:00Z",
    "endDate": "2026-11-10T17:00:00Z",
    "maxCapacity": 50
}

###

### Activate the draft (uses the ID from the previous response)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events(ID={{createEvent.response.body.ID}},IsActiveEntity=false)/AdminService.draftActivate
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Publish the activated event
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events(ID={{createEvent.response.body.ID}},IsActiveEntity=true)/AdminService.publish
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ================
### Dynamic values — fresh data on every run
### ================

### Create an event with a generated UUID and timestamped title
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/admin/Events
{{adminAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "ID": "{{$guid}}",
    "title": "Smoke Test {{$datetime iso8601}}",
    "startDate": "2026-12-01T09:00:00Z",
    "endDate": "2026-12-01T17:00:00Z",
    "maxCapacity": 50
}

### ================
### Registration service
### ================

### Browse events (limited fields)
GET {{host}}/odata/v4/registration/Events
{{attendeeAuth}}

### Create a registration
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/registration/register
{{attendeeAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Alice",
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "eventId": "6ec0bd7f-11c0-43da-975e-2a8ad9ebae0b"
}

### Register with missing fields (should return multiple errors)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/registration/register
{{attendeeAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "eventId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6"
}

### Register for a draft event (should fail — not published)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/registration/register
{{attendeeAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Alice",
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "eventId": "a0eebc99-9c0b-4ef8-bb6d-6bb9bd380a11"
}

### Register successfully for TechEd (published, has capacity)
POST {{host}}/odata/v4/registration/register
{{attendeeAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "Alice",
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "eventId": "6ec0bd7f-11c0-43da-975e-2a8ad9ebae0b"
}
